HEADWORD: Modillion
<hw>Mo*dil"lion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>modillon</ets>, It. <ets>modiglione</ets>. Cf. <er>Module</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>The enriched block or
horizontal bracket generally found under the cornice of the Corinthian
and Composite entablature, and sometimes, less ornamented, in the Ionic
and other orders; -- so called because of its arrangement at regulated
distances.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Modiolar</ent>⟦br⟧
